text.section:
Each motor club shall provide to its members:
a service contract;
a membership card; and
the following information:
the exact name of the motor club;
the street address of the motor club's home office;
the street address of the motor club's principal place of business in the State;
the telephone numbers of the motor club's home and business offices; and
a description of the motor club services or benefits to which the member is entitled.

A service contract may not:
contain inconsistent, ambiguous, or misleading clauses, exceptions, or conditions that deceptively affect the risk purported to be assumed or the motor club service to be performed;
contain an inequitable provision that does not have a substantial benefit to the member;
require the payment of fees that are unreasonable in relation to the motor club service agreed to be performed; or
offer reimbursement only, unless the contract clearly states that emergency road service will not be provided.
